answer.explanation:
Formula for partially filled capacitor: C =  rac{\epsilon_0 A}{d - t + t/K}
Here t = d/5.
C =  rac{\epsilon_0 A}{d - d/5 + d/(5K)} =  rac{\epsilon_0 A}{4d/5 + d/(5K)}
C =  rac{\epsilon_0 A}{d(4/5 + 1/5K)} =  rac{C_0}{(20K + 5)/25K} ... simplifying fraction:
Denominator factor = 4/5 + 1/(5K) = (4K+1)/(5K).
C = C_0 / [(4K+1)/(5K)] = C_0 * [5K / (4K+1)]
